  <ns3:title xmlns:ns3="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">FS-TD-003/3.2.4/Validate penalty calculation logic - simple interest calculation.</ns3:title>
  <ns3:description xmlns:ns3="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">At the account level, when penalty calculation logic is set to simple interest then the following calculation must take place: 

Penalty Amount = (Amount x Number of penalty days x Interest Rate) / 365 

In case of partial redemption, Amount = (Redemption amount – Capitalized Unpaid Interest)

In case of full redemption, Amount = (Current Balance – Capitalized Unpaid Interest)

For example, let us take the case of $50,000 being partially redeemed from a term deposit account where the capitalized unpaid interest is zero. The rate of interest is 1% and the interest penalty is 60 days. 

Penalty Amount = (50,000 x 60 x 0.01) / 365 = $82.19

Success Criteria: Penalty amount is $82.19</ns3:description>
